Acting on whatever solution that seems the best to you is the best advice I can give because simply not doing so will just repeat the process of worry and thought and that’s how you overthink. Don’t continue thinking too hard know you’re solutions and just act.

Just because we don’t like an outcome or can’t see how something plays out in a positive way for us doesn’t mean that we don’t act on it we get so caught up in wanting to feel good about every little thing that we forget we need adversity to grow as a person

But over thinking I believe starts to happen when we either can’t find the solutions or don’t like the outcomes we see so we begin to worry about it until our focus is dragged somewhere else and then when we have a moment of silence again we think of the same unresolved issue

That’s really not the case it’s okay to feel those negative emotions and you sort through the issues in your life. I know for me when I sit and think after all the problem solving I feel a bit of happiness and optimism
